  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Typhoon Mangkhut Recovery Project (Phase Two)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Unconditional Cash Transfer will enable Typhoon Mangkhut affected families from barangay Dimapula, Sapinit, Dilakit, Dipudo, Dibulos, Dimapnat, Dimasalansan, to address their immediate needs. These will give vulnerable families the power to prioritize and decide where cash will be spent in accordance with contextual need of the family. Priority is given to farmers, fisher folk, solo parents, IP, PWD, and others as recommended by CSC during the criteria setting workshop.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to respond to the immediate needs of communities in the Municipality of Divilacan, Isabela affected by Typhoon Mangkhut and make them safe and more resilient to disaster, through:
1. Unconditional Cash Transfer to 500 vulnerable families (households) in five barangays from the remote towns in Divilican, Isabela affected by Typhoon Mangkhut.
2. Community-led project in Barangay Dicaruyan, Divilacan, Isabela involving two community groups (1) barangay local government of Dicaruyan and (2) Dicaruyan Farmers association.</narrative>
  </description>
